DropInfo

DropInfo: { current: number; requested: number }

DropInfo gives info about the frame rate of the transformer

Type declaration

  • current: number

    The actual rate of the track

  • requested: number

    The rate predicted rate of the track

ErrorData

ErrorData: { error: unknown; eventMetaData: EventMetaData; function: ErrorFunction }

ErrorData. MediaProcessor error data definition.

Type declaration

  • error: unknown

    Type of unknown but moslty will be string

  • eventMetaData: EventMetaData

    Metadata of the event.

  • function: ErrorFunction

    The function in which the error occurred.

EventDataMap

EventDataMap: { error: ErrorData; pipelineInfo: PipelineInfoData; warn: WarnData }

EventDataMap. A map type for all event options from MediaProcessor. Each event will include only one type.

Type declaration

  • error: ErrorData

    Errors from the insertable streams pipeline.

  • pipelineInfo: PipelineInfoData

    Info from the insertable streams pipeline life cycle.

  • warn: WarnData

    Warnings from the insertable streams pipeline.

EventMetaData

EventMetaData: { transformerIndex: number }

EventMetaData. Some metadata of the event.

Type declaration

  • transformerIndex: number

    The transformer index in the array of transformers.

VonageMetadata

VonageMetadata: { appId: string; proxyUrl?: string; sourceType: VonageSourceType }

Specifies the addional information being sent with the telemetry collected by the library.

Type declaration

  • appId: string

    Some string identifier identifying the application using the library.

  • Optional proxyUrl?: string

    The proxy URL to route all internet traffic generated by this library. This field is optional.

  • sourceType: VonageSourceType

    Type of source using the library.

isSupported

  • isSupported(): Promise<void>

  • Check if the current browser is officially supported by the library.

    Returns Promise<void>

    The promise will resolve or reject depending whether the browser is supported or not.

setVonageMetadata

  • setVonageMetadata(metadata: VonageMetadata): void

  • Sets some metadata for telemetry. An example can be found here.

    Parameters

    • metadata: VonageMetadata

      Specifies the addional information being sent with the telemetry collected by the library. If metadata is either undefined or not set the library will not collect/send any telemetry.

    Returns void
